[stochastic] extra
------------------
The optional [stochastic] extra implements the pass^k (sampling-without-
replacement / hypergeometric) estimator, the Jeffreys Beta posterior, the
two-proportion z-test and interval-disjointness checks. The formulas and the
public-API shape of these statistics mirror, and are credited to:

    passwedge — https://github.com/hinanohart/passwedge
    Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0.

tracemin re-derives these estimators natively on numpy/scipy so the extra is
installable without a network/git dependency. When `passwedge` is importable in
the environment it is preferred automatically.

